1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:01,970
The thief is here!

2
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,480
(Episode 105)

3
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:04,580
Is anyone else here?

4
00:00:06,110 --> 00:00:07,180
Suk Hee is here.

5
00:00:14,890 --> 00:00:18,160
I haven't seen that necklace before.
Where did you get it?

6
00:00:19,690 --> 00:00:22,430
Go away, you thief!
This necklace is Suk Hee's.

7
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:24,330
Get out of here now, you thief!

8
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,430
How dare you keep calling me a thief?

9
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:32,500
What?

10
00:00:40,010 --> 00:00:43,350
"Jung Suk Hee, get this straight."

11
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:47,420
"From now on, this baby is mine."

12
00:00:47,490 --> 00:00:49,090
"I said she's my baby now!"

13
00:00:49,820 --> 00:00:51,760
What? What did you say?

14
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:54,160
Jung Suk Hee, get this straight.

15
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:56,900
From now on, this baby is mine.

16
00:00:57,230 --> 00:00:59,300
I said she's my baby now!

17
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:07,040
What did this half-wit just say?

18
00:01:07,810 --> 00:01:08,840
You remember?

19
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:11,840
Hey, Jung Suk Hee.
Did you get your memory back?

20
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,380
Did you?

21
00:01:13,510 --> 00:01:16,210
It hurts. You're hurting Suk Hee.
It hurts!

22
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:18,250
My goodness.

23
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:20,490
I thought you started to remember things.

24
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:25,690
Suk Hee.

25
00:01:25,860 --> 00:01:27,630
I'm sorry for yelling.

26
00:01:27,630 --> 00:01:30,360
It's just, you kept calling me a thief,

27
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:32,560
so I got upset too.

28
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:35,100
Look.

29
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,100
I...

30
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:41,040
brought this for you so we could make up.

31
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:44,310
Here, drink it all down, okay?

32
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:54,020
It's tasty, isn't it?

33
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,690
It's yummy. Suk Hee likes milk.

34
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:02,190
Give me the cup if you're finished.

35
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,370
- Mom, the spinach...
- Gosh.

36
00:02:10,570 --> 00:02:11,670
What are you doing here again?

37
00:02:11,670 --> 00:02:13,970
Are you here to torment my mom
with a new scheme?

38
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:17,510
Goodness.
Is that any way to treat a customer?

39
00:02:18,140 --> 00:02:19,940
I'm here to buy some side dishes.

40
00:02:20,010 --> 00:02:21,150
This is a side dish shop, you know.

41
00:02:21,210 --> 00:02:23,210
We have nothing to sell to you,
so get lost.

42
00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:25,020
Get out of here now!

43
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:28,350
- Get lost!
- Fine, I'm going!

44
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:31,560
I was leaving anyway. I'm leaving now.

45
00:02:35,730 --> 00:02:38,560
Mom, where's the salt?
We need to cleanse this place.

46
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:40,000
Good riddance.

47
00:02:42,970 --> 00:02:45,470
(Sil)

48
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,040
Eun Hye.

49
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:50,980
Please...

50
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:53,310
just be alive somewhere.

51
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,250
As long as you're alive,

52
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,620
there's nothing
your father wouldn't do for you.

53
00:03:08,290 --> 00:03:11,830
Honey, it's time for your medicine.

54
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,700
Just leave it. I'll come out and take it.

55
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:18,840
- Go on. Leave me be.
- All right.

56
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,570
You're being so irritable these days...

57
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:41,230
(Large-print Bible)

58
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:46,060
Really?

59
00:03:46,970 --> 00:03:50,030
Then he might be reunited
with his daughter soon.

60
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:52,400
Did the Chairman contact you about it?

61
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,770
No, I heard from Team Leader Jin.

62
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:58,880
Team Leader Jin seems more in the loop
than I am.

63
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,680
I hope we hear good news soon.

64
00:04:01,980 --> 00:04:02,980
Me too.

65
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:07,320
I just wish Grandfather weren't so anxious
about finding my aunt,

66
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:09,190
especially with his poor health.

67
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:10,220
I know.

68
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:13,360
So, are you excited
about getting a new aunt?

69
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:16,430
Of course.
It's wonderful having a new family member.

70
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,100
That reminds me.

71
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:23,400
I'd like to cook for your mother sometime.
Would that be all right?

72
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:25,270
That's a great idea.

73
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:28,840
Are you trying to score points
with your mother-in-law?

74
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:31,210
What a thoughtful idea.

75
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:33,780
My thoughts follow my heart.

76
00:04:34,410 --> 00:04:39,220
Tell me what dishes your parents like.
Do they have any favorites?

77
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:41,350
Don't worry. They're not picky eaters.

78
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:44,060
They'd be thrilled
just to have you over for dinner.

79
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:46,060
Come on, I can't do that.

80
00:04:47,230 --> 00:04:48,660
It's my brother. Hold on a second.

81
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:51,200
Hey, what's up?

82
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:55,500
What? Chae Hwa Young came to the shop?

83
00:05:00,970 --> 00:05:03,840
Team Leader Jin. Where's Chae Hwa Young?

84
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:06,540
She said she was stepping out for work.

85
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:08,980
I never told her to go out.
Where would she go?

86
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:10,250
Is that so?

87
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:12,980
Come to think of it, she has been acting
a little strange lately.

88
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:17,990
I think Chae Hwa Young has been
slacking off to run her own errands.

89
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:19,990
That's right.

90
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:23,390
Chae Hwa Young must also know
the Chairman's daughter is alive.

91
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:26,130
What are you talking about?

92
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:28,870
When the Chairman's sister-in-law
came by last time,

93
00:05:28,930 --> 00:05:30,440
she and my mom had a huge fight.

94
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,500
Chae Hwa Young was there,

95
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,270
and she heard
that the Chairman's daughter was alive.

96
00:05:34,510 --> 00:05:37,510
So, Chae Hwa Young knows my aunt is alive.

97
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:41,110
If the Chairman finds his real daughter,
Chae Hwa Young won't just sit back.

98
00:05:41,910 --> 00:05:43,880
Everything she's worked for at Dream
would go up in smoke.

99
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:46,320
You'd be taking a hit too, you know.

100
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,290
You and Ma Seo Rin are
just his granddaughters,

101
00:05:49,290 --> 00:05:50,820
but this woman is his actual daughter.

102
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:53,890
At her age, she's probably married
with a husband and a son,

103
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:56,130
so where do you think his shares
will all go?

104
00:05:57,730 --> 00:06:00,330
When you think about it,
they’ve been left high and dry too.

105
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:02,200
And that goes without saying
for my mom and me.

106
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,600
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

107
00:06:09,510 --> 00:06:11,510
If Chae Hwa Young finds my aunt first,

108
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,640
she'll try to sabotage everything.

109
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:17,680
What if she's out looking for
my aunt right now?

110
00:06:27,230 --> 00:06:29,860
This is a picture the Chairman
was secretly looking at in his study.

111
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:40,400
Why is the embroidery on the bib
in the photo the same...

112
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,840
as the one on the newborn gown?

113
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:47,080
On the off chance that Jung Suk Hee
is his real daughter,

114
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:48,610
I have to get rid of that first.

115
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:50,180
No, wait.

116
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:53,820
If Seo Rin or Oh Jang Mi
were to see that photo,

117
00:06:54,290 --> 00:06:55,550
they'd definitely...

118
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,760
connect it to Jung Suk Hee.

119
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,690
No, that can't happen. Absolutely not.

120
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:16,840
Oh, shit.

121
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:28,550
What?

122
00:07:30,290 --> 00:07:32,520
Where did she put her newborn gown?

123
00:07:33,090 --> 00:07:34,590
It was here last time.

124
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:38,230
She hid it away
like it's some great treasure.

125
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,750
Look at this.

126
00:07:58,580 --> 00:08:01,050
The four-leaf clover embroidery
is right here, plain as day.

127
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:05,920
It's practically screaming
that Jung Suk Hee is his daughter.

128
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:17,130
- Mom, what are you doing in here?
- What do you mean?

129
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:20,040
I just came in to check on you.

130
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:28,810
That was weird.

131
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:37,520
That was a close call.

132
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:40,890
Seo Rin is so sharp that...

133
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,790
she's definitely going to be suspicious.

134
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:47,270
No. She won't notice that
her newborn gown is missing.

135
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:54,370
Jung Suk Hee and Chairman Ma...

136
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:58,210
A DNA test will tell me for sure.

137
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:03,310
Jun Ho, are you still this busy?

138
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,150
Here's a change of clothes for you.

139
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:11,160
Thank you, Mother.

140
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:15,260
Baek Ho and Jang Mi are coming over...

141
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:17,400
for a casual dinner this weekend,

142
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:18,860
and I was wondering...

143
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:21,370
if it'd be awkward for you to join us.

144
00:09:23,570 --> 00:09:27,610
Lately, I've been wondering
if I'm even part of this family.

145
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,640
What are you talking about?

146
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:34,450
I was only that way
because I wanted you to get over her.

147
00:09:36,410 --> 00:09:37,780
In this world,

148
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:41,390
there are some things you just can't have,
no matter how much you want them.

149
00:09:41,990 --> 00:09:43,250
If you get hung up on it,

150
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:45,620
you'll only end up
hurting yourself, Jun Ho.

151
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:48,390
If you truly love someone,

152
00:09:48,490 --> 00:09:51,960
you have to respect their feelings.

153
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,130
Jang Mi...

154
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,430
says she's in love with Baek Ho.

155
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:59,070
Then, why can't you let Father go?

156
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:02,310
- Jun Ho.
- Even though you were married,

157
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:04,510
Father says he doesn't want
to be with you anymore.

158
00:10:05,010 --> 00:10:08,680
So isn't holding on like this
just torturing him?

159
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:12,180
On top of that,
you're harassing Chae Hwa Young, too.

160
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,620
You can't compare this to that.

161
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:17,990
We were married,
and we built our family on trust.

162
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:19,890
Your father was the one
who broke that trust.

163
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:22,660
And Chae Hwa Young
played a part in it, too.

164
00:10:24,430 --> 00:10:28,270
When you break up after just dating,
all you have to do is get over it.

165
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:30,230
But an affair...

166
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:35,010
is a terrible sin that destroys
the souls of every single family member.

167
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,240
How could you say that to me?

168
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:40,810
You're not blameless either.

169
00:10:41,850 --> 00:10:43,480
Why couldn't you keep our family together?

170
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:47,550
Why did you just stand by and let things
get this bad between Baek Ho and me?

171
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:49,620
Does this make any sense to you?

172
00:10:50,220 --> 00:10:53,790
Your two sons are rivals
over the same woman.

173
00:10:54,330 --> 00:10:57,190
But in a situation like this,
how can you possibly give them...

174
00:10:57,730 --> 00:10:58,830
your blessing?

175
00:11:00,030 --> 00:11:02,670
- Jun Ho, this is...
- I don't want to hear any more.

176
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:04,670
The answer is obvious, anyway.

177
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:07,740
Because I'm the black sheep
of this family.

178
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:10,880
Because I'm not a real Kang.

179
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:15,010
Isn't that it?

180
00:11:24,260 --> 00:11:25,260
I can't believe him...

181
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:28,230
That really hurt.

182
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:40,240
Hello...

183
00:11:41,310 --> 00:11:42,970
Were you here to see General Manager Kang?

184
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:45,310
Yes. Please, excuse me.

185
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:47,010
Wait.

186
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,680
Thank you for the suit.

187
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:50,920
Manager Lee.

188
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,320
By any chance, is there a place...

189
00:11:55,620 --> 00:11:56,850
where I can be alone...

190
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,930
and just have a good cry?

191
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:16,370
If you cry too much,
you'll get a sore throat.

192
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,210
Here, drink this.

193
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:20,240
It should help you calm down.

194
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:22,450
Thank you.

195
00:12:24,450 --> 00:12:26,520
I'm sorry you had to see me like this.

196
00:12:29,220 --> 00:12:30,450
Did you and General Manager Kang...

197
00:12:30,990 --> 00:12:32,520
have a disagreement?

198
00:12:42,430 --> 00:12:44,240
He said Kang Nam Bong's affair...

199
00:12:45,770 --> 00:12:47,300
was all my fault.

200
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:50,910
He asked me why I didn't
keep the family together...

201
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:53,710
and told me to let his father go now.

202
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:57,580
Am I...

203
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:01,220
really the one at fault here?

204
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:03,620
Lawyer Han.

205
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:07,530
Is this all that amounted...

206
00:13:08,730 --> 00:13:10,060
from a marriage of over 30 years?

207
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:16,500
What have I been doing with my life?

208
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:19,700
I feel the same way.

209
00:13:20,370 --> 00:13:22,640
For over 30 years,

210
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:25,180
I've wondered what I ever was
to Chae Hwa Young.

211
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:27,680
What was I doing all that time?

212
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:30,050
That's exactly how I feel.

213
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:35,050
I've...

214
00:13:35,490 --> 00:13:38,720
been terribly inappropriate
in front of you, Manager Lee.

215
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:42,330
I understand why Jun Ho is...

216
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:44,600
acting like that to me now.

217
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:49,800
He lost the woman he loves
to his own brother.

218
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:51,500
That's true.

219
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,640
Jun Ho may seem tough on the outside,

220
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:57,270
but on the inside,
he's a kind and sensitive young man.

221
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:58,980
Yes, that's right.

222
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:05,680
You know him so well, Manager Lee.

223
00:14:09,690 --> 00:14:11,090
I should get going now.

224
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:13,160
Thank you for the tea.

225
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,600
I feel dizzy. Just a second.

226
00:14:21,830 --> 00:14:24,240
I'm sorry, I just need
to lean on you for a second.

227
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:29,840
Please, you need to stop crying.

228
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,210
You're going to collapse at this rate.

229
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:40,150
What is going on here?

230
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,860
Lee Kang Hyuk, are you out of your mind?

231
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:47,120
Who do you think you're holding?

232
00:14:47,660 --> 00:14:48,990
And in my office, of all places.

233
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:51,000
That's rich coming from you.

234
00:14:52,330 --> 00:14:53,330
What?

235
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,170
It wasn't long ago...

236
00:14:55,870 --> 00:14:58,670
that I walked in on you and my husband
hugging in this very office,

237
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:01,210
professing your love for each other.

238
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,340
Don't you remember?

239
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:06,480
- What are you talking about?
- It's a misunderstanding.

240
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:09,250
Lawyer Han was feeling very upset,

241
00:15:09,310 --> 00:15:12,320
so she was just taking a moment
to compose herself.

242
00:15:12,380 --> 00:15:15,350
And you two had to be holding each other
for her to feel better?

243
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:18,220
That's enough.
There's no need to raise your voice.

244
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:21,030
Manager Lee didn't do anything wrong,

245
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:22,890
so if you have a problem,
take it up with me.

246
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:24,900
So now you're his lawyer?

247
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:26,800
You know what they say,
a guilty mind suspects everyone.

248
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,830
When a man and a woman are together,
do you always assume it's an affair?

249
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:32,240
I don't know what you think you're doing,

250
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:34,740
but Manager Lee has long been...

251
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:37,710
my right-hand man.
He's practically my shadow.

252
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:42,210
So don't you get any funny ideas
and stay away from my Manager Lee.

253
00:15:42,350 --> 00:15:43,950
I'm warning you.

254
00:15:44,050 --> 00:15:47,150
You're quite the player, aren't you?

255
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:51,490
So where does my Nam Bong
rank on your list?

256
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:54,120
- Why, you little...
- That's enough, Lawyer Han.

257
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,260
If you're finished here,

258
00:15:56,990 --> 00:15:58,460
I'd appreciate it if you would leave.

259
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,400
I have to get back to work.

260
00:16:01,370 --> 00:16:02,870
Fine. I'll go.

261
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,900
Listen, Chae Hwa Young.

262
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:08,410
Let me make one thing perfectly clear.

263
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:10,870
Kang Nam Bong and Kang Jun Ho...

264
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:13,340
are still my family.

265
00:16:14,210 --> 00:16:16,150
You haven't won them over yet.

266
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:17,410
So,

267
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:21,450
you're the one who needs a reality check.

268
00:16:22,050 --> 00:16:23,150
Get a grip.

269
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:24,860
If you're not careful,

270
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:28,330
you'll end up losing the only person
who's still by your side.

271
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:35,300
Who does she think she is,
running her mouth like that?

272
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:37,430
And what's your deal?

273
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:40,900
Why would you let me see you with her
and provoke me like that?

274
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:46,240
I've only ever been involved in your work,
never your personal life.

275
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:48,880
Isn't that what you wanted?

276
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:50,780
When I repeatedly tried to warn you...

277
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:54,220
about your relationship
with Professor Kang,

278
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:56,620
you just ignored me.

279
00:16:56,820 --> 00:17:00,260
So, it's okay for you,
but not for me? Is that it?

280
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:03,030
So you're getting back at me?
Is that what this is?

281
00:17:03,090 --> 00:17:05,530
I'm asking you to stay out
of my personal life.

282
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:07,800
So Lawyer Han...

283
00:17:08,670 --> 00:17:10,300
is part of your "personal life" now?

284
00:17:12,140 --> 00:17:13,470
If you have no further instructions,

285
00:17:14,070 --> 00:17:15,470
please call for me when you do.

286
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:17,840
Kang Hyuk.

287
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:22,480
What's the rush?

288
00:17:23,050 --> 00:17:24,680
You know I came here to see you.

289
00:17:25,050 --> 00:17:26,050
What is it?

290
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:29,990
Have I done something to upset you?

291
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:34,290
Of course.

292
00:17:34,830 --> 00:17:36,230
You must have been terribly hurt.

293
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:40,360
But you know I can't do this without you.

294
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,470
Kang will go back
to Han Young Ja in the end.

295
00:17:44,470 --> 00:17:46,040
You think I don't know that?

296
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:49,570
You're the only one
who will stay by my side forever.

297
00:17:54,810 --> 00:17:55,980
I just submitted...

298
00:17:56,610 --> 00:18:00,450
a DNA test
for Jung Suk Hee and Chairman Ma.

299
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:05,020
I'm not hiding anything from you.

300
00:18:05,990 --> 00:18:08,930
There are no secrets between us.

301
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:10,560
Right?

302
00:18:35,290 --> 00:18:36,290
Ma Eun Hye...

303
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:39,460
There must be more information
about her somewhere.

304
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:47,260
I'm sure Secretary Kim
filed a report on this.

305
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:51,840
Here it is.

306
00:18:52,270 --> 00:18:53,370
(Child Personal Information Record)

307
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,510
Park Young Mi.

308
00:18:55,210 --> 00:18:56,210
Young Mi?

309
00:18:57,370 --> 00:18:58,610
The child with the necklace.

310
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:04,520
What's with the Bible?

311
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:09,720
Mom.

312
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:12,020
What are you doing in here?

313
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:13,590
Gosh, Seo Rin.

314
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:17,390
What evil scheme are you plotting
in Grandfather's study?

315
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:22,170
Seo Rin, it's not what you think.
I was just looking for some documents.

316
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:23,230
Stop lying.

317
00:19:23,770 --> 00:19:25,570
I'm telling Grandfather
everything right now.

318
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:28,040
Grandfather!

319
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:30,810
Ma Seo Rin, quiet down.

320
00:19:31,210 --> 00:19:32,780
This isn't just about me.

321
00:19:32,910 --> 00:19:35,610
Your entire life is on the line.

322
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:39,780
I don't believe a word you say.
I'm not falling for it again.

323
00:19:40,020 --> 00:19:41,590
You stole something from my room,
didn't you?

324
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:43,550
What was it you stole from my room?

325
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,620
- Let me go!
- Be quiet.

326
00:19:47,690 --> 00:19:48,890
I said let go!

327
00:19:56,570 --> 00:19:57,600
Why, you little...

328
00:19:57,970 --> 00:20:00,100
I go easy on you,
and now you think you can take advantage?

329
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:02,740
What gives you the right to hit me?

330
00:20:03,010 --> 00:20:05,910
- I don't trust you anymore, Mom.
- Why are they making such a scene?

331
00:20:05,910 --> 00:20:08,110
I'll take over the company
and get Jun Ho on my own.

332
00:20:08,780 --> 00:20:10,480
Sure. Like you could ever do that.

333
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,520
You think I'm incompetent too?

334
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,950
That's just because I haven't tried.

335
00:20:14,020 --> 00:20:16,320
But if I put my mind to it,
I can do a better job than you.

336
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:20,060
Seo Rin, this isn't about your abilities.

337
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:22,630
Your grandfather has
a biological daughter.

338
00:20:24,460 --> 00:20:27,330
What are you talking about?
Grandfather has a biological daughter?

339
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,170
They all thought the daughter...

340
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,970
your grandmother gave birth to was dead,
but apparently, she's alive.

341
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:35,310
That's why your grandfather
has been running around frantically...

342
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:37,910
trying to find her.

343
00:20:38,110 --> 00:20:42,110
So what if my aunt is alive?
I'm the heir, what does it matter?

344
00:20:42,210 --> 00:20:43,910
It changes the entire line of succession.

345
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:46,720
Imagine how much he'll dote on
his own flesh and blood.

346
00:20:47,150 --> 00:20:51,920
Especially a daughter he held just once
and spent his life thinking was dead.

347
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:54,390
Put yourself in your grandfather's shoes.

348
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:57,630
Wouldn't he want to give her
everything he has?

349
00:20:57,930 --> 00:20:58,930
Shit.

350
00:20:59,330 --> 00:21:02,200
So then what were you looking for
in the study?

351
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:05,000
Secretary Kim is searching for
your grandfather's biological daughter.

352
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:08,670
I was trying to see
how far he's gotten in his investigation.

353
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:10,870
And it's putting us in a dire position.

354
00:21:10,870 --> 00:21:11,880
He's found her already?

355
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:13,840
What do you think you're doing over there?

356
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:17,050
What brings you here, Lawyer Kang?

357
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:18,880
I'm here to see Ms. Ma Seo Rin.

358
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:23,350
- Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?
- Why is that guy here to see you?

359
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:25,960
Shit. How should I know?

360
00:21:32,130 --> 00:21:33,300
I see you two are together.

361
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:39,670
What? Has the Chairman already found
his biological daughter?

362
00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:43,570
I thought he didn't even know her name
or which orphanage she was left at.

363
00:21:43,710 --> 00:21:47,480
He only knew he had a daughter.
How could he have found her this fast?

364
00:21:47,710 --> 00:21:51,150
That's ridiculous.
Why are you so worked up about it?

365
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:54,690
You're not Chairman Ma's mistress,
nor are you in the family registry.

366
00:21:54,950 --> 00:21:56,890
And it's not like
he promised you anything, either.

367
00:21:57,090 --> 00:22:01,660
We should team up and do everything
in our power to stop this,

368
00:22:02,230 --> 00:22:05,000
- and you're here twisting the knife?
- That's right.

369
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:07,230
Let's say we do team up.

370
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:10,300
But what can you even do?

371
00:22:10,370 --> 00:22:13,640
Of course there is.
I can be your inside source.

372
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:17,470
You have to do a good job as an informant
for me to even consider trusting you.

373
00:22:18,710 --> 00:22:19,710
Trust me?

374
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:25,250
Do you really know something about
the Chairman's biological daughter?

375
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,680
The murder weapon, the wrench.

376
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:30,420
You know where it is, don't you,
Ma Seo Rin?

377
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:33,320
Shit. I already told you I don't know.

378
00:22:34,860 --> 00:22:36,160
As if Oh Jang Mi wasn't enough,

379
00:22:36,460 --> 00:22:39,660
are you two taking turns
ganging up on me now?

380
00:22:39,860 --> 00:22:43,100
You know better than anyone
what a monster CEO Chae is.

381
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:46,770
That's why you and Jang Mi
tried to take her down.

382
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,210
Am I wrong?

383
00:22:48,710 --> 00:22:50,110
Don't you spare any thoughts...

384
00:22:50,610 --> 00:22:53,180
for your own birth mother
and your sister, Jang Mi?

385
00:22:54,010 --> 00:22:57,210
- Don't you feel that family bond?
- I'm only human. Of course I feel it.

386
00:22:57,650 --> 00:23:01,490
But what good is that bond?
Is it going to take care of me?

387
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:05,820
Will some sacred bond get my position back
or keep Jun Ho by my side?

388
00:23:06,060 --> 00:23:09,530
I chose my present and future
over some messy past.

389
00:23:10,190 --> 00:23:15,100
And to do that, I need Chae Hwa Young
to make me her perfect successor.

390
00:23:15,170 --> 00:23:16,270
Don't kid yourself.

391
00:23:16,730 --> 00:23:21,200
Once you're no longer useful to CEO Chae,
she'll discard you without hesitation.

392
00:23:21,610 --> 00:23:24,710
Actually, you'll be lucky
if she only throws you away.

393
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:27,110
You could just disappear without a trace.

394
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:30,910
Didn't Jang Mi tell you
what happened to Ssangkal,

395
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:32,680
Chae Hwa Young's attack dog?

396
00:23:38,120 --> 00:23:39,190
Ma Seo Rin.

397
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:42,260
Please, tell me about the wrench.

398
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:46,260
All I know is that it's buried
in the mountain behind the company.

399
00:23:46,330 --> 00:23:47,360
Where exactly?

400
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:50,270
I secretly mapped out
some possible spots...

401
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:53,900
where Manager Lee might have buried it...

402
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,410
and saved it on a USB drive.

403
00:23:55,910 --> 00:23:58,940
- As an insurance policy, just in case.
- And that's the USB that's missing?

404
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:01,010
It's a USB that looks like a lipstick,

405
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:04,850
but when I got home after the incident,
it was gone without a trace.

406
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:06,950
Shit. And Oh Jang Mi says
she doesn't know anything either.

407
00:24:07,950 --> 00:24:11,190
Did Chae Hwa Young figure it out
and get to it first?

408
00:24:12,460 --> 00:24:13,460
Thank you...

409
00:24:15,290 --> 00:24:19,230
for pulling strings so my Jun Ho
wouldn't be imprisoned for kidnapping.

410
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:21,000
You don't have to thank me.

411
00:24:21,570 --> 00:24:22,600
Thank Jang Mi.

412
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:28,070
She's the one who ultimately convinced me,
and the one who protected your man.

413
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:31,840
Jang Mi again? Shit.

414
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:35,980
Oh Jang Mi, you just have to play
the saint, don't you?

415
00:24:45,460 --> 00:24:47,460
What on earth are you planning?

416
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:51,490
What more could you possibly plan
now that you've been kicked out?

417
00:24:51,860 --> 00:24:54,930
Kang Jun Ho.
You still don't get it, do you?

418
00:24:55,630 --> 00:24:59,740
Now is not the time to be losing your head
over some worthless girl like Oh Jang Mi.

419
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:04,070
Don't worry about me.
You should worry about yourself.

420
00:25:05,010 --> 00:25:07,080
Chairman Ma is looking
for his biological daughter.

421
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:08,980
What?

422
00:25:09,050 --> 00:25:13,120
I've spent the last 30 years
pouring my all into this company.

423
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:17,820
How dare he try to ruin everything for me
when I'm so close to what I deserve?

424
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:19,420
Not on my watch.

425
00:25:21,590 --> 00:25:22,860
What are you talking about?

426
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:26,560
- His biological daughter?
- Chairman Ma's daughter is alive.

427
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:31,400
Right now, Chairman Ma is desperately
searching everywhere for her.

428
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:33,300
This is our chance.

429
00:25:33,870 --> 00:25:35,810
We have to make a move
with the board of directors...

430
00:25:35,810 --> 00:25:37,270
or do whatever it takes.

431
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:41,610
If we don't, we'll lose all of Dream
to Chairman Ma's daughter,

432
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:43,980
and we'll be thrown out onto the street.

433
00:25:45,350 --> 00:25:46,380
So...

434
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:49,720
- What's the plan?
- Listen carefully.

435
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:51,920
Here's my plan.

436
00:25:52,420 --> 00:25:55,490
While Chairman Ma is distracted
looking for his daughter,

437
00:25:55,990 --> 00:26:00,560
we'll siphon off the company shares
by laundering them via a shell company.

438
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:05,300
You take control of the company,
staying within the bounds of the law.

439
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:09,610
I'll be the one to get my hands dirty
and fight in the mud.

440
00:26:20,250 --> 00:26:25,660
I feel I haven't been a proper host
since you arrived in Korea.

441
00:26:26,420 --> 00:26:28,790
This is an embroidered norigae
handmade stitch by stitch...

442
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:30,260
by a master artisan I regularly go to.

443
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:32,860
It's a true intangible
cultural heritage piece.

444
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:35,830
And this...

445
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:39,870
is some agarwood.
It's to help restore your vitality.

446
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:43,740
Things like this don't mean anything
to me anymore.

447
00:26:45,780 --> 00:26:47,880
All I care about is my niece, Eun Hye.

448
00:26:48,610 --> 00:26:50,780
I just want to find her soon.

449
00:26:50,780 --> 00:26:52,550
I'm sure you will.

450
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:55,850
That's why you need
to take care of yourself.

451
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:57,350
Thank you anyway.

452
00:26:57,890 --> 00:27:01,360
Also, I have someone on my team
who's excellent at finding people.

453
00:27:02,230 --> 00:27:05,630
Is there anything else you can tell me
that might help?

454
00:27:06,930 --> 00:27:10,630
I suppose that's why you're the CEO.

455
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:16,970
Actually, this wasn't on the banner.

456
00:27:24,210 --> 00:27:28,350
I have to take care of myself
if I'm going to see our Eun Hye.

457
00:27:29,450 --> 00:27:30,450
That's right.

458
00:27:31,290 --> 00:27:35,660
This old body has to hold on
so I can hug my poor daughter.

459
00:27:41,330 --> 00:27:43,400
Chairman, I believe we've found her.

460
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:45,400
We've finally found her.

461
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:48,000
What? You found her?

462
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,440
You...

463
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:53,840
found my daughter, Eun Hye?

464
00:28:29,050 --> 00:28:30,610
(The First Man)

465
00:28:30,780 --> 00:28:32,880
Where on earth is that lipstick?

466
00:28:33,150 --> 00:28:35,720
It's the only thing
that gives me any power.

467
00:28:36,020 --> 00:28:38,960
What if Oh Jang Mi took it
and is just playing innocent?

468
00:28:39,390 --> 00:28:40,420
This is impossible.

469
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:43,530
How can Jung Suk Hee be his real daughter?

470
00:28:43,530 --> 00:28:45,430
How can this be true?

471
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:47,830
We found a woman named Park Young Mi
working in a restaurant.

472
00:28:47,900 --> 00:28:50,130
We also learned she was
in an orphanage as a child.

473
00:28:50,470 --> 00:28:53,270
That's her. This is my Eun Hye!

474
00:28:57,510 --> 00:28:59,510
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
